{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}} {{Infobox writer | name = Jean-Baptiste-Pierre Courcelles | image = | imagesize = | caption = | pseudonym = | birth_name = {{nobreak|Jean-Baptiste-Pierre Jullien de Courcelles}} | birth_date = 14 September 1759 | birth_place = [[Orléans]], France | death_date = 24 July 1834 | death_place = [[Saint-Brieuc]], [[Brittany]] | occupation = [[genealogist]], historian | nationality = | period = | genre = | subject = | movement = | notableworks = | influences = | influenced = | signature = | website = }}
'''Jean-Baptiste-Pierre Jullien de Courcelles''' (14 September 1759 – 24 July 1834) was a French historian and [[genealogist]].{{r|bnf}} He was born in [[Orléans]] and died at [[Saint-Brieuc]], now in the [[Côtes d'Armor]] [[département]] of [[Brittany]]. He published several historical and genealogical works, and was a correspondent of the {{Interlanguage link multi|Académie d'Orléans|fr|3=Académie d'Orléans|lt=Société académique d'Orléans}}.{{r|bnf}} He was chief administrator of the charitable Asile Royal de la Providence in Paris, president of the [[hospices]] of Orléans, and a knight of the Papal [[Order of the Golden Spur]].{{r|bnf}}
== Publications ==
The principal works of Courcelles are:
* ''Dictionnaire historique et biographique des généraux français depuis le XIe siècle'', Paris: l'auteur, 1820–1823. In nine volumes: :* [https://archive.org/stream/dictionnairehis06unkngoog#page/n9/mode/2up Volume 1]; [https://archive.org/stream/dictionnairehis01unkngoog#page/n9/mode/2up Volume 2]; [https://archive.org/stream/dictionnairehis24unkngoog#page/n9/mode/2up Volume 3]; [https://archive.org/stream/dictionnairehis03unkngoog#page/n9/mode/2up Volume 4]; [https://archive.org/stream/dictionnairehis02unkngoog#page/n9/mode/2up Volume 5]; [https://archive.org/stream/dictionnairehis08unkngoog#page/n9/mode/2up Volume 6]; [https://archive.org/stream/dictionnairehis25unkngoog#page/n11/mode/2up Volume 7]; [https://archive.org/stream/dictionnairehis12unkngoog#page/n9/mode/2up Volume 8]; [https://archive.org/stream/dictionnairehis14unkngoog#page/n11/mode/2up Volume 9]
* ''Dictionnaire universel de la noblesse de France'', Paris: au bureau général de la noblesse de France, 1820–1822. In five volumes: :* [https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_OIkGAAAAQAAJ Volume 1], A–L; [https://archive.org/stream/dictionnaireuni00unkngoog#page/n9/mode/2up Volume 2], M–Z; [https://archive.org/details/dictionnaireuni02courgoog Volume 3], A–M (supplement); [https://archive.org/stream/dictionnaireuni00courgoog#page/n9/mode/2up Volume 4], N-Z (supplement); [https://archive.org/stream/dictionnaireuni01courgoog#page/n9/mode/2up Volume 5] A-Z (supplement)
* ''Histoire généalogique et héraldique des pairs de France, des grands dignitaires de la couronne, des principales familles nobles du royaume, et des maisons princières de l'Europe'', Paris: l'auteur, 1822–1833. In twelve volumes: :* [http://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k854915z/f27.image. Volume 1]; [https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_HUb5OX3a0NgC Volume 2]; [https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_5GvV-w9Q2GoC Volume 3]; [https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_SKVBAAAAcAAJ Volume 4]; [https://archive.org/details/histoiregnalogi02courgoog Volume 5]; [https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_2jB8y91_UOAC Volume 6]; [https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_EJ6oYQCH66MC Volume 7]; [https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_I0sWAAAAYAAJ Volume 8]; [https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_96VBAAAAcAAJ Volume 9]; [https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_53UWVkP4YrgC Volume 10]; [https://books.google.fr/books?id=fksWAAAAYAAJ&printsec=frontcover&hl=fr#v=onepage&q&f=false Volume 11]; [https://archive.org/details/histoiregnalogi01courgoog Volume 12]
