'''Rhiannon Ash''' is a British classical scholar, specialising in [[Latin litrature]] and [[Tcititus]]. She is Professor of [[Roman historiography|Roman Historiography]] in the [[Faculty of Classics, University of Oxford|Faculty of Classics]], [[University of Oxford]], and a [[Fellow (Oxbridge)|Fellow]] of [[Merton College, Oxford]].<ref name=OU/> She was formerly a [[lecturer]] at the Department of Greek and Latin at [[University College, London]].

== Career ==
Ash completed undergraduate study at Oxford. She subsequently studied for an [[Master of Arts (Oxbridge and Dublin)|MA]] in Toronto, before obtaining a [[DPhil]] from the University of Oxford.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.classics.ox.ac.uk/rhiannonash.html|title=Rhiannon Ash - Classics|website=www.classics.ox.ac.uk|language=en|access-date=2018-01-22}}</ref>

Her primary area of research interest in Latin prose literature of the [[Roman Empire|Imperial Era]], especially that of [[Tacitus]]. She writes variously on ancient epistles, Greek and Roman biography, battle narratives, and [[Pliny the Elder]], among other subjects.

